AUGUSTA, Maine — Officials with the Maine Department of Health and Human Services were at the State House Wednesday to brief lawmakers on how the department investigates fraud across its programs.

The meeting was requested by the Legislature’s Health and Human Services Committee two weeks ago and comes amid [increased calls from Republican lawmakers](/article/news/politics/maine-politics/maine-republicans-investigation-alleged-mainecare-fraud-maine/97-1ab4b8f1-0df2-4c16-9705-255d3189191f) to investigate fraud, particularly following the [audit of Gateway Community Services](/article/news/investigations/state-audit-federal-probe-fraud-gateway-community-services-maine-medicaid/97-c4abeb4d-634e-4b0c-b079-4e3d0059bd5c).

Although fraud has become a [top priority for State House Republicans](/article/news/politics/maine-politics/maine-lawmakers-first-day-new-legislative-session-augusta-republican-democrat/97-c281b925-e1a4-4d02-be00-10eb709d35de), legislators were told they would not hear details about any specific cases during the briefing. Instead, the hearing focused on how DHHS is structured to detect and investigate fraud, what each oversight unit is responsible for, and how many staff members are assigned to that work.

Lawmakers heard from leaders of three separate auditing and investigative groups within the department. Those include the Division of Audit, the Fraud Investigation and Recovery Unit, and the MaineCare Program Integrity Unit.

The Division of Audit reviews spending across the entire department, including contracts within DHHS and MaineCare. The Fraud Investigation and Recovery Unit focuses on individuals accused of defrauding the department, such as cases involving stolen SNAP benefits. The MaineCare Program Integrity Unit investigates providers enrolled in MaineCare and was the unit responsible for auditing [Gateway Community Services](/article/news/local/courts-news/counseling-organization-in-maine-denies-accusations-of-mainecare-fraud-calling-reporting-false-dhhs/97-72645b6f-dc23-438f-a5df-fd278202fa59).

